data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":252,"item_id":"msg_0ca5affed7bd1568006933b45bb54081968f27f621d390e36c","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"Contoso Electronics has a Whistleblower Policy designed to maintain a safe and transparent working environment. Here's a summary of the policy:\n\n- **Definition**: A whistleblower is someone who reports illegal, unethical, or non-compliant activities within Contoso Electronics.\n  \n- **Reporting Procedures**: To report an incident:\n  1. Contact the Human Resources Department.\n  2. Email the Compliance Officer at **compliance@contoso.com**.\n  3. Call the Compliance Hotline at **1-800-555-1212**.\n  Reports should be as detailed as possible, including the time, date, people involved, what happened, and any supporting evidence.\n\n- **Anonymity**: Reports can be made anonymously by calling the Compliance Hotline.\n\n- **Retention Policy**: Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited. Disciplinary actions (up to and including termination) will be taken against employees who retaliate.\n\n- **Confidentiality and Investigation**: Whistleblowers’ identities will be kept confidential as permitted by law, and all reported incidents will be investigated thoroughly.\n\nThis policy is designed to promote ethical conduct, transparency, and a safe workplace culture.","logprobs":[]}

